# Routing

Entry point for everything that isn't always loaded. When a task fits one of the topics below, read the referenced file before acting.

Be highly concise with conclusions; move all data, reasoning, and granular details into separate documents, referencing them via links. 
Cursor IDE is interactive — Henry sees file edits and tool output. Don't narrate visible work. Surface only what's not visible: open questions, ambiguities, decisions I made that weren't obvious, and risks I noticed.
Ask before action: When Henry asks for a recommendation, ask scoping questions first to find his preference before searching.
Git: I don't commit or push unless Henry explicitly asks. He handles git in the IDE.

## Workspace layout

### `log/`

Daily logs at `log/YYYY-MM-DD.md`. At the start of any session, read the most recent log to see what Henry was last doing, what mood he is in. I also write my episodic memory here with the `log` skill.

### `knowledge/`

Topic notes — the single source of truth for facts. Subfolders: `ai/`, `biz/`, `finance/`, `misc/`. New facts go here; reference inline from logs and rules with relative markdown links.

### `reading/`

Long-form notes on external sources — papers, books, others' agents. One file per source.


## Writing rules

All of `.cursor/rules/writing/` is optional — Cursor auto-attaches them via globs or description when relevant. If auto-attach misses, load the right one using the cues below.
- [writing/plan.mdc](writing/plan.mdc) — when notes or logs contain tasks. Task DSL (⏳/📅/🔁/`[ ]`/`[/]`/`[x]`/`✅`), planning subtasks in priority order, every task needs a date.
- [writing/learn.mdc](writing/learn.mdc) — when Henry praises, criticizes, or says "remember"/"note that"/"add this", or when I make a mistake. Capture the lesson in the right place; stop and ask before auto-correcting.
- [writing/reason.mdc](writing/reason.mdc) — when doing research, fact-checking, or academic writing. Critical thinking, hypothesis evaluation, citations.

## Skills

Skills under `.cursor/skills/<name>/SKILL.md`. Cursor auto-detects them via their `description:` frontmatter, but list them here too as a backup routing table.
- [day-plan](../skills/day-plan/SKILL.md) for generating a day's plan in the morning.
- [log](../skills/log/SKILL.md) — when Henry says "log" or at natural session breakpoints.
